# Documentation Organization Standards

## Documentation Location Rules

### Rule: NO Markdown Files in Project Root (Except README.md)

**CRITICAL:** Only `README.md` should exist in the project root directory. All other markdown files MUST be organized in the `docs/` directory structure.

```bash
✅ ALLOWED in root:
- README.md (main project documentation)

❌ FORBIDDEN in root:
- Any other .md files
- Implementation summaries
- Test results
- Feature documentation
- Architecture docs
```

## Documentation Directory Structure

```
docs/
├── api/                  # API endpoint documentation
├── features/            # Feature guides and overviews
├── implementation/      # Implementation summaries for major features
├── testing/             # Test results and verification reports
├── architecture/        # System architecture and design documents
├── privacy/             # Privacy architecture and compliance
├── guides/              # User guides and tutorials
├── development/         # Development setup and guidelines
├── troubleshooting/     # Common issues and solutions
└── archive/             # Historical/deprecated documentation
```

## File Placement Guidelines

### API Documentation → `docs/api/`

**When:** Documenting API endpoints, request/response formats, authentication

**Files:**
- `{feature}_endpoint.md` - API reference for endpoints
- `{FEATURE}_QUICK_START.md` - Getting started guides
- `README.md` - API documentation index

**Example:**
```bash
docs/api/profile_endpoint.md
docs/api/link_blocks_endpoint.md
docs/api/LINK_BLOCKS_QUICK_START.md
```

### Feature Overviews → `docs/features/`

**When:** High-level feature documentation for users and developers

**Content:**
- Feature overview and purpose
- User-facing capabilities
- Use cases and examples
- Configuration options
- Future enhancements

**Example:**
```bash
docs/features/LINK_BLOCKS.md
docs/features/SEARCH_FILTERS.md
```

### Implementation Summaries → `docs/implementation/`

**When:** Completing major features (3+ days of work), architectural changes

**Content:**
- What was built and why
- Files created/modified
- Database schema changes
- API endpoints added
- Security/privacy implementation
- Performance characteristics
- Testing and verification
- Configuration requirements

**Example:**
```bash
docs/implementation/LINK_BLOCKS_IMPLEMENTATION.md
docs/implementation/PRIVACY_SYSTEM_IMPLEMENTATION.md
```

### Test Results → `docs/testing/`

**When:** Recording test execution results, verification reports

**Content:**
- Integration test results
- Manual verification reports
- Performance benchmarks
- Issues found during testing
- Test coverage summary

**Example:**
```bash
docs/testing/TEST_RESULTS_LINK_BLOCKS.md
docs/testing/PERFORMANCE_BENCHMARK_2026_02.md
```

### Architecture → `docs/architecture/`

**When:** Documenting system design, data models, technical architecture

**Content:**
- System architecture diagrams
- Database schema documentation
- Design patterns and rationale
- Component interactions
- Scalability considerations

**Example:**
```bash
docs/architecture/profile-database-schema.md
docs/architecture/PERFORMANCE_OPTIMIZATIONS.md
docs/architecture/SPA_RENDERING.md
```

### Privacy & Compliance → `docs/privacy/`

**When:** Privacy architecture, GDPR/CCPA compliance, data handling

**Content:**
- Privacy system design
- Compliance protocols
- Data encryption methods
- Anonymization strategies
- Legal requirements

**Example:**
```bash
docs/privacy/PRIVACY_ARCHITECTURE.md
docs/privacy/LEGAL_VAULT_PROTOCOL.md
```

### User Guides → `docs/guides/`

**When:** Step-by-step instructions, deployment guides, best practices

**Content:**
- Deployment guides
- Configuration tutorials
- Best practices
- Usage examples
- Production recommendations

**Example:**
```bash
docs/guides/PRODUCTION_JS_MINIFICATION.md
docs/guides/DOCKER_HEALTH_CHECK_BEST_PRACTICES.md
```

### Development Docs → `docs/development/`

**When:** Developer-focused technical documentation

**Content:**
- Development setup
- Coding guidelines
- Technical references (MongoDB, CMake, etc.)
- Development tools
- Internal APIs

**Example:**
```bash
docs/development/MONGODB_CPP_GUIDE.md
docs/development/template-development.md
```

### Troubleshooting → `docs/troubleshooting/`

**When:** Problem-solving guides, debugging, fixes for common issues

**Content:**
- Issue descriptions and symptoms
- Root cause analysis
- Step-by-step solutions
- Prevention strategies
- Related issues

**Example:**
```bash
docs/troubleshooting/FLOWER_TIMEZONE_CONFIGURATION.md
docs/troubleshooting/FIX_MONGODB_WARNING.md
```

### Archive → `docs/archive/`

**When:** Deprecating or superseding documentation

**Content:**
- Outdated documentation
- Historical records
- Previous implementation summaries
- Deprecated feature docs

**Example:**
```bash
docs/archive/DOCS_ORGANIZATION_COMPLETE.md
docs/archive/OLD_API_v1.md
```

## Naming Conventions

### File Names

**API Documentation:**
```bash
{feature}_endpoint.md           # lowercase with underscore
{FEATURE}_QUICK_START.md        # UPPERCASE for guides
```

**Implementation Summaries:**
```bash
{FEATURE}_IMPLEMENTATION.md     # UPPERCASE
```

**Test Results:**
```bash
TEST_RESULTS_{FEATURE}.md       # Prefix TEST_RESULTS_
PERFORMANCE_BENCHMARK_{date}.md
```

**Architecture:**
```bash
{feature}-{aspect}.md           # lowercase with hyphen
{FEATURE}_SUMMARY.md            # UPPERCASE for summaries
```

**Troubleshooting:**
```bash
FIX_{ISSUE_NAME}.md             # Prefix FIX_ for solutions
{ISSUE}_ANALYSIS.md             # Suffix _ANALYSIS for deep dives
{FEATURE}_CONFIGURATION.md      # Configuration guides
```

### Directory Names

All lowercase, use hyphens for multi-word names (except existing conventions):
```bash
api/                    # ✅ single word
architecture/          # ✅ single word
implementation/        # ✅ single word
troubleshooting/       # ✅ single word
```

## README Files

Every directory MUST have a `README.md` file:

**Required Content:**
1. **Directory purpose:** What this folder contains
2. **File list:** Brief description of each file
3. **When to use:** Guidelines for adding new files
4. **Related docs:** Links to related documentation

**Template:**
```markdown
# [Directory Name]

[Brief description of what this directory contains]

## Contents

### [Category]

**[filename.md](./filename.md)** - Description
- Key point 1
- Key point 2

## Purpose

[What types of documentation belong here]

## When to Create [Document Type]

[Guidelines for when to add new files]

## [Document Type] Template

[Optional template for consistency]

## Related Documentation

- **Other Dir:** `docs/other/` - Description
```

## Documentation Workflow

### Creating New Documentation

1. **Determine type:** What kind of document is this?
2. **Choose location:** Use guidelines above to select directory
3. **Check README:** Read the directory's README.md
4. **Name properly:** Follow naming conventions
5. **Use template:** If available, use the template in README
6. **Update README:** Add entry to directory's README.md
7. **Link from root:** If major, link from `docs/README.md`

### Moving Existing Documentation

```bash
# ❌ WRONG - Files in project root
/root/search-engine-core/FEATURE_IMPLEMENTATION.md

# ✅ CORRECT - Organized in docs/
/root/search-engine-core/docs/implementation/FEATURE_IMPLEMENTATION.md
```

**Steps:**
1. Identify current location and file type
2. Determine correct location using guidelines
3. Move file: `mv file.md docs/{directory}/`
4. Update any references to the file
5. Update directory README.md
6. Update docs/README.md if needed

### Deprecating Documentation

1. Move to `docs/archive/`
2. Add deprecation notice at top:
   ```markdown
   > **DEPRECATED:** This document has been superseded by [new-doc.md](../new-location/new-doc.md)
   ```
3. Remove from current directory's README
4. Add to archive/README.md with deprecation date

## Cross-Referencing

### Linking Between Docs

**Use relative paths:**
```markdown
✅ CORRECT:
See [API Documentation](../api/endpoint.md)
See [Feature Guide](../features/FEATURE.md)

❌ WRONG:
See docs/api/endpoint.md
See /root/search-engine-core/docs/features/FEATURE.md
```

### Linking to Implementation

From API docs, always link to:
1. Implementation summary (if exists)
2. Feature guide (if exists)
3. Test results (if exists)

**Example:**
```markdown
## References

- **Implementation:** [Link Blocks Implementation](../../implementation/LINK_BLOCKS_IMPLEMENTATION.md)
- **Feature Guide:** [Link Blocks Overview](../../features/LINK_BLOCKS.md)
- **Test Results:** [Link Blocks Tests](../../testing/TEST_RESULTS_LINK_BLOCKS.md)
```

## Documentation Maintenance

### Regular Cleanup (Monthly)

- [ ] Check for .md files in project root (except README.md)
- [ ] Verify all directories have README.md
- [ ] Update docs/README.md with new files
- [ ] Archive outdated documentation
- [ ] Fix broken cross-references
- [ ] Update "Last Updated" dates

### After Major Features

When implementing a major feature:
1. Create implementation summary in `docs/implementation/`
2. Create API documentation in `docs/api/`
3. Create feature guide in `docs/features/` (if user-facing)
4. Document test results in `docs/testing/`
5. Update `docs/README.md` with new links
6. Update relevant directory READMEs

### Version Control

- Commit documentation with related code changes
- Use descriptive commit messages: `docs: add link blocks implementation summary`
- Keep documentation in sync with code

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

### ❌ Don't Do This

```bash
# Creating .md files in project root
touch FEATURE_DOCS.md

# Random file names without convention
touch my-notes.md
touch temp-doc.md

# Missing README in new directories
mkdir docs/new-category/
# (forgot to create README.md)

# Absolute paths in links
[Link](file:///root/search-engine-core/docs/api/endpoint.md)
```

### ✅ Do This Instead

```bash
# Use proper directory structure
touch docs/implementation/FEATURE_IMPLEMENTATION.md

# Follow naming conventions
touch docs/api/feature_endpoint.md
touch docs/testing/TEST_RESULTS_FEATURE.md

# Always create README
mkdir docs/new-category/
touch docs/new-category/README.md

# Use relative paths
[Link](../api/endpoint.md)
```

## Quick Reference

| Document Type | Location | Naming | Example |
|--------------|----------|--------|---------|
| API Reference | `docs/api/` | `{feature}_endpoint.md` | `profile_endpoint.md` |
| Quick Start | `docs/api/` | `{FEATURE}_QUICK_START.md` | `LINK_BLOCKS_QUICK_START.md` |
| Feature Guide | `docs/features/` | `{FEATURE}.md` | `LINK_BLOCKS.md` |
| Implementation | `docs/implementation/` | `{FEATURE}_IMPLEMENTATION.md` | `LINK_BLOCKS_IMPLEMENTATION.md` |
| Test Results | `docs/testing/` | `TEST_RESULTS_{FEATURE}.md` | `TEST_RESULTS_LINK_BLOCKS.md` |
| Architecture | `docs/architecture/` | `{feature}-{aspect}.md` | `profile-database-schema.md` |
| Privacy Docs | `docs/privacy/` | `{FEATURE}.md` | `PRIVACY_ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| User Guide | `docs/guides/` | `{FEATURE}_GUIDE.md` | `PRODUCTION_JS_MINIFICATION.md` |
| Dev Guide | `docs/development/` | `{topic}.md` | `MONGODB_CPP_GUIDE.md` |
| Troubleshoot | `docs/troubleshooting/` | `FIX_{ISSUE}.md` | `FIX_MONGODB_WARNING.md` |
| Deprecated | `docs/archive/` | (original name) | `OLD_FEATURE_DOCS.md` |

## Enforcement

- **Pre-commit hook:** Check for .md files in root (except README.md)
- **CI/CD:** Verify documentation structure in pipeline
- **Code review:** Ensure documentation is properly placed
- **Monthly audit:** Review and reorganize as needed

